00:10:05,670 --> 00:10:06,751
Okay, second question.

267
00:10:06,751 --> 00:10:10,654
Questions that test your memorization.

268
00:10:11,743 --> 00:10:14,525
So this is like API questions, unless you need an API expert,

269
00:10:14,525 --> 00:10:16,586
like deep API questions.

270
00:10:16,586 --> 00:10:18,607
And so I was once asked, this is one of the stupidest

271
00:10:18,607 --> 00:10:22,890
questions I ever got, was what does cster do on the

272
00:10:22,890 --> 00:10:24,011
string class?

273
00:10:24,011 --> 00:10:24,391
Really?

274
00:10:24,391 --> 00:10:24,471
OK.

275
00:10:26,077 --> 00:10:28,479
Mathematical formulas, I don't like,

276
00:10:28,479 --> 00:10:30,040
Bezier curve is another good one.

277
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:32,603
I don't, I couldn't, I couldn't recite that right now,

278
00:10:32,603 --> 00:10:33,664
but I can look it up in two seconds,

279
00:10:33,664 --> 00:10:36,286
and I can tell you why or when to apply

