00:27:12,940 --> 00:27:15,581
was aimed at people who had a little bit more experience.

668
00:27:15,581 --> 00:27:17,262
And I'm just wondering if there were things

669
00:27:17,262 --> 00:27:20,143
you could say more to someone who's fresh out,

670
00:27:20,143 --> 00:27:22,665
entry level, who is also going through this process.

671
00:27:22,665 --> 00:27:25,766
Like trying to get a job, basically, that sort of thing?

672
00:27:25,766 --> 00:27:27,647
Right, yeah, like maybe they've done a game project

673
00:27:27,647 --> 00:27:31,589
as an undergraduate, they've done the AI on that.

674
00:27:32,030 --> 00:27:38,612
Not like they've worked on some shipped triple-a title, but they would certainly love to break in and they love it. Yeah

